{ This position is ALWAYS winning, no matter whose turn it is.

In other words, OPPOSITION is irrelevant.

In other words, the KEY SQUARES for a pawn in the 5th rank are the 3 in front of it. } { [%csl Bd6,Be6,Bf6] }
1. Kd6 Kd8 2. e6 Ke8 3. e7 { [%cal Re8f7] } 3... Kf7 4. Kd7 { [%csl Ge8][%cal Ge7e8] } *


[Event "King & Pawn vs King: >>>> Pawn in 5th, king in front (b)"]
