{ This is a tricky case. It is winning, but the only way to win is Kh6 (Kf6 is not a winning method, although it does not spoil the win).

... } { [%cal Gg6h6,Rg6f6] }
1. Kh6 (1. Kf6 Kh7! 2. Kf7 (2. g6+?? { This is a draw now } 2... Kh8! { and now every move is a draw } 3. g7+ (3. Kf7 { stalemate } { [%csl Rh7,Rg7,Rg8] }) (3. Kf5 Kg7 $10 { [%csl Gg7,Gg8][%cal Gg7g8,Gg8g7] }) 3... Kg8 { [%csl Gg7][%cal Gf6g7] } 4. Kg6 { stalemate }) 2... Kh8 { [%cal Gg5g6] } 3. Kg6 (3. Kf6 Kh7 { just repeating }) (3. g6?? { stalemate }) 3... Kg8 { Going back to the initial position, therefore not spoiling the win, but also not making any progress. }) 1... Kh8 2. g6 Kg8 3. g7 { [%cal Rg8f7] } 3... Kf7 4. Kh7 { [%cal Gg7g8] } *


