{ When a pawn did not reach the 5th rank yet, its KEY SQUARES are 2 squares in front of it.

Therefore in this position, the only way to win is the plan Ke5 and Kd6. } { [%csl Be6,Bd6,Bf6][%cal Gf4e5,Ge5d6] }
1. Ke5 { Black would love to play Ke7 now, but it's one square short. } { [%csl Re7,Bd6,Be6,Bf6][%cal Rg8e7,Ge5d6] } (1. Kf5?? Kf7 { [%csl Re6,Rf6,Rg6,Bd6] } 2. Ke5 Ke7 $10 { [%csl Rd6,Re6,Rf6] }) (1. Kg4?? { [%csl Bd6,Be6,Bf6][%cal Rg8f7,Gg4f5] } 1... Kf8 { [%csl Bf6,Be6,Bd6][%cal Rg4f5,Gf8f7] } 2. Kf4 { [%csl Be8,Re4][%cal Rf8e7,Gf4e5,Rf8f7,Gf4f5,Rf8g7,Gf4g5,Bf8e8] } 2... Ke8! { [%csl Bd6,Be6,Bf6] } 3. Ke5 (3. Kf5 Kf7 { [%csl Rg6,Rf6,Re6,Bd6] }) 3... Ke7 $10 { [%csl Rf6,Re6,Rd6] }) (1. Kg5?? Kg7! { [%csl Rf6,Rg6,Rh6,Be6,Bd6] } 2. Kf5 (2. e5 { [%csl Rg5,Re5] } 2... Kf7 3. Kf5 Ke7 { [%csl Re5][%cal Gf5e5] }) 2... Kf7 $10 { [%csl Rg6,Rf6,Re6,Bd6] }) 1... Kf7 2. Kd6 { [%csl Gd6,Ge4] } 2... Kf8 3. e5 Ke8 4. Ke6 { [%csl Bd7,Be7,Bf7,Ge6,Re8] } 4... Kd8 5. Kf7 { [%cal Ge5e6,Ge6e7,Ge7e8] } *


