{ As we just mentioned, any pawn that didn't reach the 5th rank (in other words, still in your half of the board) has KEY SQUARES 2 ranks in front of it.

White wins by directly aiming at b5 here. } { [%csl Bd5,Bc5,Gb5][%cal Gf1e2,Ge2d3,Gd3c4,Gc4b5,Rg8f7,Rf7e6,Re6d6] }
1. Ke2 { [%csl Gb5,Bc5,Bd5][%cal Ge2d3,Gd3c4,Gc4b5,Rg8f7,Rf7e6,Re6d6] } 1... Kf7 { [%csl Gb5,Bc5,Bd5][%cal Rf7e6,Re6d6,Ge2d3,Gd3c4,Gc4b5] } 2. Kd3 { [%csl Gb5,Bd5,Bc5][%cal Rf7e6,Re6d6,Gd3c4,Gc4b5] } 2... Ke6 { [%csl Gb5,Bc5,Bd5][%cal Re6d6,Gd3c4,Gc4b5] } 3. Kc4 { [%csl Gb5,Bd5,Bc5][%cal Re6d6,Gc4b5] } 3... Kd6 { [%csl Gb5,Bc5,Bd5,Rd6][%cal Gc4b5] } 4. Kb5 { White reached a KEY SQUARE, White wins. } { [%csl Bd5,Bc5,Gb5,Rd6] } 4... Kc7 5. Kc5 { [%csl Bb6,Bc6,Bd6,Rc7,Gc5] } 5... Kd7 { [%csl Bd6,Bc6,Gb6] } 6. Kb6 { etc } *


