[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

{ This example is exceptional.
Right now WE LOST THE OPPOSITION.

But thanks to the fact that the pawn is covering f7, we can regain it.
Do you see how? } { [%csl Bd7,Be7,Rf7][%cal Ge6f7] }
1. Kf5! { Yes!
Black now can't play Kf7 to keep the OPPOSITION. } { [%csl Rf7] } 1... Kf8 (1... Kg8 2. Kg6 { [%csl Gg6,Rg8] } (2. Kf6 Kf8 3. e7+ Ke8 4. Ke6) 2... Kf8 3. Kf6 { [%csl Gf6,Rf8] } 3... Ke8 4. e7 { [%cal Re8d7] }) 2. Kf6 { Of course! } { [%csl Gf6,Rf8] } 2... Ke8 3. e7 { [%cal Re8d7] } *


