[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

{ Black's king will run all the way down to take the a2 pawn.

Do you remember the KEY SQUARE to save this one? }
1. Kh7! { Yes!
Our KEY SQUARE is c2 so we need our king to stay close enough to the opponent's so we will be able to answer Kb2 with Kd3. } { [%csl Bc2,Ra2][%cal Rf6e5,Re5d4,Rd4c3,Rc3b2,Rb2a2,Gh7g6,Gg6f5,Gf5e4,Ge4d3,Gd3c2] } (1. Kg8?? { Noooo.
The KEY SQUARE was c2. Now we're too far to reach it (blue: 6 moves) when Black takes on a2 (red: 5 moves). } { [%csl Bc2,Ra2][%cal Rf6e5,Re5d4,Rd4c3,Rc3b2,Rb2a2,Bg8f7,Bf7e6,Be6d5,Bd5c4,Bc4c3,Bc3c2] }) 1... Ke5 { [%csl Bc2] } 2. Kg6 { [%csl Bc2] } 2... Kd4 { [%csl Bc2] } 3. Kf5 { [%csl Bc2] } 3... Kc3 { [%csl Bc2] } 4. Ke4 { [%csl Bc2] } 4... Kb2 { [%csl Bc2] } 5. Kd3 { [%csl Bc2] } 5... Kxa2 { [%csl Bc2] } 6. Kc2 { [%csl Gc2,Ra2][%cal Rb2b3,Rb2b1] } 6... Ka1 { [%csl Ra1,Gc2][%cal Rb2b3,Rb2b1] } 7. Kc1 { [%csl Gc1,Ra1][%cal Rb1b2,Rb2b1] } 7... Ka2 { [%csl Ra2,Gc1][%cal Rb1b2,Rb2b1,Ba2b3] } 8. Kc2 { [%csl Gc2,Ra2][%cal Rb2b3,Rb2b1] } 8... Ka1 { [%csl Ra1,Gc2][%cal Rb2b3,Rb2b1] } 9. Kc1 { [%csl Gc1,Ra1][%cal Rb1b2,Rb2b1] } 9... a2 { [%csl Ra1,Gc1][%cal Rb1b2,Rb2b1] } 10. Kc2 { Stalemate.
Good job! } { [%csl Gc2,Ra1] } *


