[UTCTime "17:07:46"]
[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

{ Yes, the position is losing, but we know we can save it if our opponent doesn't find/know the right plan.

What's the most resilient defense? }
4. Kb1 Kc3 5. Ka2!? { Correct.
Now Black can only win with Kc2. } 5... Kc2 6. Ka1 Kb3 7. Kb1 { And it's the 2nd time we reach this position.
Black MUST play Ka3 here to win or else we will have a 3-fold repetition. } { [%csl Gb1,Rb3] } 7... Kc3? 8. Ka2! { Again, yes!
And in this case it's not even losing anymore, because we will get the 3-fold repetition. } 8... b3+ { Let's say Black wants to avoid the repetition and tries b3+.
How do we draw now? } 9. Ka1! { Yes!
Now Kc2 is stalemate, while other king moves allow us in front of the pawn already (Kb2). } (9. Kb1?? { Noooooo 🤦 } { [%cal Gb3b2] }) 9... b2+ 10. Kb1 Kb3 { Draw.
Great job. } *


