[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/pepellou"]
[FEN "8/6b1/5k2/8/P3K1P1/8/8/8 w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2019.02.27"]
[UTCTime "10:09:01"]
[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

{ White to play and win }
1. a5 Bf8 2. Kd5 { Correct!
We needed to prevent Bc5. } { [%csl Rf8,Gd6,Gc5][%cal Gd5c5,Gd5d6] } (2. Kd4 { Nooooo!
Yes, you stopped Bc5, but white's king is in a bad square now. Bb4 is in time to defend, since it forces a6 and Be1 exploits our king position. } 2... Bd6 { [%cal Gd6b8] } 3. a6 Bb8) (2. g5+ { Noooooo!
The right idea but with bad timing. Black cannot take the pawn, but after Ke6 instead, we still need to stop Bc5 and black has time to enter our 'a' pawn square with the king, therefore ensuring the draw. } { [%cal Gf6e6] } 2... Ke6 { [%cal Rf8c5] } 3. Kd4 Kd6 { [%csl Gg7][%cal Ra5a8,Ra5d5,Rd5d8,Rd8a8,Gf8g7] }) 2... Bh6 3. g5+! { Bravo!!
Now the bishop will be blocked by its own king and will not be able to freely change diagonal as it did so far. } (3. Kd4 { Noooooo!
Bad place for the king. Now Bd2 forces a6 and then Be1 exploits our king position. Draw. }) (3. Ke4 { That repeats the position. It's still winning, as you can guess, but you're going in circles. }) 3... Bxg5 { [%cal Gg5e3] } (3... Kxg5 4. a6 { [%cal Ga6a7,Rh6e3] }) 4. Ke4 { [%csl Ge3,Gf4][%cal Ge4e3,Ge4f4,Rg5e7,Re7c5] } (4. Kd4 { Nooooo!
Black is in time to draw with Bd2 or Bh4, using the unfortunate position of our king, or with Bf4 and Bb8. }) 4... Bh4 { [%cal Gh4f2] } 5. Kf3 { Bravo!! Well done! } { [%csl Gf2,Gg3,Rf4,Re3][%cal Gf3f2,Gf3g3,Rh4g5,Rg5e3] } *


