[Event "Endgames: from zero to hero 💪: Rule of the square"]
[Date "2019.03.04"]
[Result "*"]
[Variant "Standard"]
[ECO "?"]
[Opening "?"]
[StudyName "Endgames: from zero to hero 💪"]
[ChapterName "Rule of the square"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/tU7iyXX4/txkgvBgQ"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/pepellou"]
[FEN "8/8/8/6k1/1P6/6K1/8/8 w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2019.03.04"]
[UTCTime "21:30:53"]

{ It's a geometrical hint to determine whether a king can stop a passed pawn or not. We draw a square with pawn square (b4) and the promotion square (b8). We complete the square towards the king (in this case to the right).

An easy way to get the 3rd corner is to draw a diagonal from the pawn to the eighth rank (in blue).

RULE: the king must be INSIDE the square to stop the pawn.

. } { [%csl Gb4,Gb8,Gf4,Gf8,Rg5][%cal Gb4b8,Bb4f8,Gb8f8,Gf8b8,Gb8b4,Gf4b4,Gb4f4,Gf8f4,Gf4f8] }
1. b5 { .
the square gets smaller each step the pawn is pushed, so the king can never enter
. } { [%csl Ge5,Gb5,Gb8,Ge8,Rg5][%cal Gc8e8,Gc8b8,Gb7b8,Gb7b5,Ge7e8,Ge7e5,Gd5e5,Gd5b5] } 1... Kf5 { [%csl Ge5,Gb5,Gb8,Ge8,Rf5][%cal Ge7e8,Ge7e5,Gd5e5,Gd5b5,Gb7b8,Gb7b5,Gc8e8,Gc8b8] } 2. b6 { [%csl Gd6,Gb6,Gb8,Gd8,Rf5][%cal Gc8d8,Gc8b8,Gb7b8,Gb7b6,Gc6d6,Gc6b6,Gd7d8,Gd7d6] } 2... Ke6 { [%csl Gd6,Gb6,Re6,Gd8,Gb8][%cal Gb7b8,Gb7b6,Gc6d6,Gc6b6,Gd7d8,Gd7d6,Gc8d8,Gc8b8] } 3. b7 { [%csl Gb7,Gc7,Gc8,Gb8,Re6][%cal Gb7b8,Gb8b7,Gb7c7,Gc7b7,Gc7c8,Gc8c7,Gc8b8,Gb8c8] } 3... Kd7 { [%csl Rd7,Gc7,Gb7,Gb8,Gc8][%cal Gc7c8,Gc8c7,Gc7b7,Gb7c7,Gb7b8,Gb8b7,Gb8c8,Gc8b8] } 4. b8=Q { [%csl Gb8,Rd7] } *


