{ We call it DOMINATION when all the moves of a piece are controlled by the opponent's pieces. Knights are especially vulnerable to this, as shown in this diagram where the 4 black knights are dominated.

For some nice domination puzzles check out the following study:
-[[ https://lichess.org/study/yDaY35d8 ]]- } { [%csl Rc2,Rb3,Rc5,Ra5,Rd6,Rd8,Rh2,Rg3,Re3,Rd2,Rg5,Rf6,Rf8][%cal Gc3c2,Gc3b3,Gd5d8,Gd5a5,Gf4c1,Gf4h2,Gf5h5,Gf5f8] }
