[UTCTime "13:15:39"]

{ We call FORTRESS a position where, despite being material down, you can hold the draw. Being material down means you have to be careful though, so fortresses usually imply a drawing method (not every move draws).

In this example, white has a FORTRESS, and the drawing method consists in keeping the king in the corner: }
1. Kh1! { Black needs to stop attacking g1 or it would be a stalemate now, but whatever black does, there's no way to force white's king out of the corner: } (1. Kf1?? { this would break the fortress and now black wins } 1... Ba7 { [%csl Rg1,Rf2,Rg2,Re2] } 2. Ke1 Kg2 { [%csl Rh2][%cal Gg2h2] }) 1... Bc7 2. Kg1 Bb6+ 3. Kh1 Ke3 4. Kg1 Ke2+ 5. Kh1 { draw } *


