[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2019.03.04"]
[UTCTime "21:30:08"]

{ When a pawn did not reach the 5th rank yet, its key squares are 2 squares in front of it (see the blue squares).

Therefore in this position, the only way to win (i.e. the only way to access a blue square) is the plan Ke5 and Kd6.

. } { [%csl Be6,Bd6,Bf6][%cal Gf4e5,Ge5d6] }
1. Ke5 { [%csl Re7,Bd6,Be6,Bf6][%cal Rg8e7,Ge5d6] } (1. Kf5?? Kf7 { [%csl Re6,Rf6,Rg6,Bd6] } 2. Ke5 Ke7 $10 { [%csl Rd6,Re6,Rf6] }) (1. Kg4?? { [%csl Bd6,Be6,Bf6][%cal Rg8f7,Gg4f5] } 1... Kf8 { [%csl Bf6,Be6,Bd6][%cal Rg4f5,Gf8f7] } 2. Kf4 { [%csl Be8,Re4][%cal Rf8e7,Gf4e5,Rf8f7,Gf4f5,Rf8g7,Gf4g5,Bf8e8] } 2... Ke8! { [%csl Bd6,Be6,Bf6] } 3. Ke5 (3. Kf5 Kf7 { [%csl Rg6,Rf6,Re6,Bd6] }) 3... Ke7 $10 { [%csl Rf6,Re6,Rd6] }) (1. Kg5?? Kg7! { [%csl Rf6,Rg6,Rh6,Be6,Bd6] } 2. Kf5 (2. e5 { [%csl Rg5,Re5] } 2... Kf7 3. Kf5 Ke7 { [%csl Re5][%cal Gf5e5] }) 2... Kf7 $10 { [%csl Rg6,Rf6,Re6,Bd6] }) 1... Kf7 2. Kd6 { [%csl Gd6,Ge4] } 2... Kf8 3. e5 Ke8 4. Ke6 Kd8 5. Kf7 { For more info on K+P vs K:
-[[ https://lichess.org/study/EsB7U2A9 ]]- } { [%cal Ge5e6,Ge6e7,Ge7e8] } *


