[ChapterName "::::[ Practical endgames ]:::::"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/tU7iyXX4/SA3FGVbt"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/pepellou"]
[FEN "8/8/8/8/8/8/8/8 b - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2019.03.11"]
[UTCTime "19:48:02"]

{ Practical endgames are endgames that really happened in real games.

A practical endgame is something between a middlegame and a theoretical endgame: rules of endgames apply but many possibilities still exist.

Instead of knowing who is winning/drawing (and how) the usual things to determine in a practical endgame are:

1) Who has the advantage (and why)
2) What are the plans for each side

We're going to cover here some insightful examples of practical endgames and link to other studies with more complex material to study. }
 *


