[Event "Castling rules in Chess960: The rules"]
[Date "2019.02.10"]
[Result "*"]
[Variant "Chess960"]
[ECO "?"]
[Opening "?"]
[StudyName "Castling rules in Chess960"]
[ChapterName "The rules"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/7LaW0hAX/rD6o9Stz"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/pepellou"]
[FEN "2r1k1r1/ppp2ppp/3p4/4p3/4P3/3P4/PPP2PPP/2R1K1R1 w KQkq - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2019.02.10"]
[UTCTime "17:05:25"]

{ The castling rules BOTH in standard chess and chess960 are as follow:

(1) King and rook must not have moved
(2) King must not be in check
(3) All squares between king and rook must be empty
(4) All squares the king has to walk through must be free of checks

Short castle always ends up with the king on the g file and the rook on the f file.

Long castle always ends up with the king on the c file and the rook on the d file. } { [%csl Gg8,Gc8,Gc1,Gg1][%cal Ge1g1,Ge1c1,Ge8c8,Ge8g8] }
 *


[Event "Castling rules in Chess960: ::::[ The Outcome ]::::::::::::"]
[Date "2019.03.13"]
[Result "*"]
[Variant "Chess960"]
[ECO "?"]
[Opening "?"]
[StudyName "Castling rules in Chess960"]
[ChapterName "::::[ The Outcome ]::::::::::::"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/7LaW0hAX/hJ5zN1MP"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/pepellou"]
[FEN "8/8/8/8/8/8/8/8 w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2019.03.13"]
[UTCTime "00:54:12"]

{ As stated in the rules, the outcome of a castling maneuver is THE SAME as in standard chess, i.e.:

- SHORT CASTLE --> king on the g file + rook on the f file.
- LONG CASTLE --> king on the c file + rook on the d file. }
 *


