{ This is the EASIEST defensive technique and a practical idea for the defending side would be to do it whenever we can. Other techniques would work in this position, but again, this is the EASIEST.

... } { [%cal Gg3g6] }
1... Rg6! { Now White is forced to push the pawn at some point to make any progress. } { [%cal Gg6a6,Gg6h6] } 2. e6 Rg1! { The king can't hide in front of the pawn now and we will be able to check him forever. } 3. Kd6 Rd1+ 4. Ke5 Re1+ 5. Kf6 Rf1+ *


