... }
1... Ra8+! 2. Kd7 Ra7+ 3. Kd8 Ra8+ 4. Kc7 Ra7+ { .
It's worth noting that, with a shorter distance (just one file), this check would be impossible.
This defensive technique teaches us one important rule:
"In order to avoid the Lucena Position, the only reliable resource is the long side"
We can draw another important conclusion:
"In most cases the defensive king should go to the short side, so that the rook can go to the long one"
