[FEN "r7/3RK1k1/4P3/8/8/8/8/8 w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2021.02.05"]
[UTCTime "14:34:36"]

1. Rd6!? { .
This is a posionous attempt, since Black is almost in zugzwang.
With White's rook so well placed, we cannot allow the king to enter the back rank, so our rook must not leave the back rank.
On the other hand, as we know (and we'll see in further chapters) if the rook leaves the a-file the ending is lost.
Therefore the rook cannot move:
... } 1... Kg6! { .
Only move. The king must wait as near from the pawn as possible.
... } (1... Ra7+?? { If we leave the back rank, White achieves Lucena: } 2. Ke8! Ra8+ 3. Rd8 Ra7 4. e7 Kf6 5. Rd6+ $18) (1... Ra1?? { Same problem as the check on a7: } 2. Ke8! Ra8+ 3. Rd8 $18) (1... Rb8?? { If we leave the a-file we also lose: } 2. Rd8! (2. Ra6? Rb7+ $10 3. Kd8 (3. Ke8 Rb8+ 4. Kd7 Rb7+ 5. Kc8 (5. Kc6 Re7 6. Kd6 Kf6) 5... Re7)) 2... Rb7+ 3. Rd7 Rb8 4. Ra7! { and we'll see in further chapters how this is lost } 4... Kg6 5. Kd6 Rb6+ 6. Kd7 $18) (1... Kg8?? { The other "waiting" move of the king is obviously losing immediately: } 2. Rd8+ Rxd8 3. Kxd8 $18 { [%cal Ge6e8] }) 2. Rd7 (2. Rd8 Ra7+ 3. Rd7 Ra8 $10) 2... Kg7! $10 { Repeating! } *


