[ChapterName "::::[ Knight vs Bishop + pawn ]::::"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/a4DRdtUx/MdBqmsal"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/pepellou"]
[FEN "8/8/8/8/8/8/8/8 w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2019.05.05"]
[UTCTime "19:26:17"]

{ The knight is not as great as the bishop to defend, so WINNING CHANCES are increased in this kind of endgame.

3 scenarios:

FIRST SCENARIO:
King blocks pawn on a square of a different color as bishop. Draw.

SECOND SCENARIO:
Both king and knight control a square in front of the pawn of a different color as bishop. Apparently a draw, but zugzwang can happen with the pawn in 6th and 7th rank.

THIRD SCENARIO:
Knight controls a square in front of the pawn, with some support from king, but blockade is not stable. Great winning chances, although complicated tactics and zugzwang might be required. }
 *


