{ This case is obviously trivial and it does not require any special understanding or study, but it's worth pointing it out, since many times when simplifying to an endgame we can foresee a position like this and know that it's immediately a draw.

... }
1... Kd8! { .
Since the bishop cannot chase the king from d8 (nor does the king or the pawn), it's an immediate draw. Black will just keep moving the knight forever. } { [%csl Rd8] } *


