[StudyName "Knight vs Bishop (wiht 1 pawn on the board)"]
[ChapterName "Stalemate resource"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/a4DRdtUx/xaRF1nKY"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/pepellou"]
[FEN "4Kn2/5Pk1/8/5B2/8/8/8/8 w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2019.05.05"]
[UTCTime "20:05:10"]

{ This position is a draw no matter who moves.

It might seem that White can triangulate Black into a zugzwang:

... }
1. Bh3 (1. Bd3 Kh8) 1... Ng6 2. Bg4 Nf8 3. Bf5 { .
Isn't this a zugzwang position?
... } 3... Kh8!! { .
No!
The stalemate trick saves the day.
Important to remember:
1) For a stalemate resource to exist, the pawn must be on the 7th rank
1) For a stalemate resource to exist, the defending king has to be on the short side of the pawn (closer to the corner of the board) } *


