[UTCTime "12:07:59"]

{ The pawn will reach the 7th rank and we cannot enter the right circuit before it happens. Also, the king is too far to help the knight.

However this is a draw.

The drawing mechanism will be a BARRIER:

... }
1. Ng3! h2 2. Kb7! { .
The knight on g3 creates a barrier!
Notice that the red squares are not available, while the blue ones would allow a fork on f1.
Black's king now needs a long way to help the pawn promote:
... } { [%csl Re2,Re4,Be3,Bd2] } 2... Kd4 { (the alternative Kc2 is also too long; this one at least tries to cut White's king progress) } { [%csl Re4,Re3,Re2,Rd2] } 3. Kc6 { [%csl Re4,Re3,Re2,Rd2] } 3... Ke5 { [%csl Re4,Re3,Re2,Rd2] } 4. Kc5 { [%csl Re4,Re3,Re2,Rd2] } 4... Kf4 { .
And now it's not about the barrier anymore. The drawing idea is to sacrifice the knight on the most annoying square: h1.
... } { [%csl Re4,Re3,Re2,Rd2] } 5. Nh1! Kf3 6. Kd4 Kg2 7. Ke3 Kxh1 8. Kf2 $10 *


