[Event "2 knights vs pawn: The general ideas"]
[Date "2022.08.17"]
[Result "*"]
[Variant "Standard"]
[ECO "?"]
[Opening "?"]
[StudyName "2 knights vs pawn"]
[ChapterName "The general ideas"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/eYXrigQn/tyIWvb9b"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/pepellou"]
[FEN "8/8/8/8/2N5/6p1/k1K3N1/8 w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2022.08.17"]
[UTCTime "09:13:07"]

{ The strong side:
- taking the pawn it's a draw (so don't)
- pawn must be blocked ASAP
- trap the opponent's king using king and 1 knight (not easy!)
- unblock the pawn only to deliver checkmate

The weak side:
- always push the pawn whenever possible
- try to avoid getting the king trapped in a corner of the board
- if we can't avoid being pushed into a corner, try for the farthest from the pawn }
 *


