[FEN "3k4/p2Np2p/q7/P5P1/2p1P1B1/2P5/8/6K1 w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2018.12.14"]
[UTCTime "09:08:55"]
[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

1. Nc5 { Correct!
The fork on b7 defends the pawn on a5 and the d6 square. The queen can only go to b5, c6 and g6 now. I'm sure you saw all the winning lines :-) } 1... Qc6 2. Ne6+ { Correct!
The king cannot walk into a discovered attack now on c8 or d7, because that would immediately lose the queen to Nd4+, so this move forces the black king to e8 while keeping the knight defended. } 2... Ke8 3. e5! { Correct!
Removing the d6 square from the queen, because she cannot go anywhere else. There are forks all over the place. Black is almost in zugzwang. } 3... a6 4. Kh2! { Correct!
All the pieces are perfect where they are, and the king needs to keep control of g2 and h1. } 4... Qe4 5. Bh5+ { Correct!
Preparing the final fork. } 5... Kd7 6. Nc5+ { Correct! Well done, puzzle solved :-) } *


