[FEN "8/2Pn4/8/3k4/K7/p5p1/8/B7 w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2018.12.14"]
[UTCTime "09:24:54"]
[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

{ We cannot promote due to a fork. Black has 2 pawns about to promote and the square the bishop has to defend both is protected. What trick do we have to save this and win? }
1. Kb5 { Correct!
It's important to avoid Nb6 to have enough counterplay. } 1... Nb6 { Oh, snap! Black plays Nb6 anyway because they want to promote on g1 with check. Clever! } 2. Kxb6 { Correct!
We need this to be able to promote. } 2... g2 { We can promote first, but black would do it with a check, regaining the initiative and the piece. How do we avoid that? } 3. Bd4 { Correct!
Black needs to walk into a terrible skewer to remove the bishop: after Kxd4, c8=Q, g1=Q we will have Qc5+ winning.
So black tries different... } 3... g1=Q 4. Bxg1 a2 { Oh no, black is going to promote again! But this time is not a check. Can we just promote? Is this Q+B vs Q winning? } 5. Bd4 { Correct!
There's a skewer on the other diagonal :-) } 5... Kxd4 6. c8=Q a1=Q 7. Qh8+ { Bravo! Puzzle solved. } *


