1. e4 { Try to avoid the Fried Liver Attack.
I want you to do the BEST way to avoid it. } 1... e5 { Great!
You don't need to give up your e5 repertoire just to avoid the Fried Liver. } (1... c5 { Hey, that's good too, the Sicilian Defense definitely avoids the Fried Liver.
But I want you to keep your e5 repertoire :-) }) (1... e6 { Hey, that's good too, the French Defense definitely avoids the Fried Liver.
But I want you to keep your e5 repertoire :-) }) (1... d5 { Hey, that's good too, the Scandinavian Defense definitely avoids the Fried Liver.
But I want you to keep your e5 repertoire :-) }) (1... c6 { Hey, that's good too, the Caro-Kann Defense definitely avoids the Fried Liver.
But I want you to keep your e5 repertoire :-) }) (1... d6 { Hey, that's good too, the Pirc Defense definitely avoids the Fried Liver.
But I want you to keep your e5 repertoire :-) }) (1... Nf6 { Hey, that's good too, the Alekhine Defense definitely avoids the Fried Liver.
But I want you to keep your e5 repertoire :-) }) (1... g6 { Hey, that's good too, the Modern Defense definitely avoids the Fried Liver.
But I want you to keep your e5 repertoire :-) }) 2. Nf3 Nc6 { Awesome!
Again, you don't need to give up your repertoire just to avoid the Fried Liver :-) } (2... Nf6 { Hey, that's good too, the Petrov Defense definitely avoids the Fried Liver.
But I want you to keep your repertoire with Nc6 :-) }) (2... d6 { Hey, that's good too, the Phillidor Defense definitely avoids the Fried Liver.
But I want you to keep your repertoire with Nc6 :-) }) 3. Bc4 Bc5 { Perfect!
This is the BEST way to avoid it. White cannot go Ng5 now and you will still be playing a typical Italian game. } (3... Nf6 { You're dangerously walking towards the Fried Liver with this move.
In the next TEST we'll walk this dangerous path, but here I want you to avoid the Fried Liver in move 3, not 5, which I would call the BEST way to avoid it ;-) }) 4. O-O { How do you proceed now? } 4... Nf6 { Of course!
With the bishop already out, there's no danger at all in going Nf6, well done :-) } 5. Ng5 { How do we solve this attack on f7 now? } { [%csl Rf7][%cal Gg5f7,Gc4f7] } 5... O-O { Perfect!! :-) } (5... d5 { This is playable, but there's a more logical move. }) *


