[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/pepellou"]
[FEN "8/p7/5R2/pkpq1p2/4rP2/KP5Q/2P2P2/8 b - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2019.06.10"]
[UTCTime "18:04:15"]
[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

{ This is not a winning position. It's Black to play and draw.
White's big threat is c4+ with checkmate ideas, that would collect material.
We don't have checks... How to save the position?

... }
1... Qd1!! { Amazing!
It's the only move that draws. The threat Qa1 with checkmate forces White's hand now. } 2. c4+ (2. Qc3 a4 (2... Qd5 3. Qe5)) 2... Rxc4 3. bxc4+ Kxc4 { Well done, although the last 2 moves were forced. We're a rook down but White's king is dominated and in a checkmating net from which their queen and rook cannot help escape. White must allow the perpetual: } 4. Kb2 Qd2+ (4... Qd4+ { Also works, but try an easier one. }) (4... Qe2+ { Also works, but try an easier one. }) 5. Kb1 Qd1+ (5... Qe1+ { Also works, but try an easier one. }) (5... Qb4+ { Also works, but try an easier one. }) 6. Kb2 Qd2+ (6... Qe2+ { Also works, but try an easier one. }) (6... Qd4+ { Also works, but try an easier one. }) *


