{ Look how this position resembles the Lucena position (chapter 11). The difference is that the black's rook is on the a-file ready to deliver checks.

This is almost the only drawn position when the pawn has reached the 7th rank and it's supported by the king.

... }
1... Ra8+! 2. Kd7 Ra7+ 3. Kd8 Ra8+ 4. Kc7 Ra7+ { .
Note that with a shorter distance (just one file), this check would be impossible.
This defensive technique teaches us one important rule:
"In order to avoid the Lucena Position, the only reliable resource is checking from the long side"
We can draw another important conclusion:
"In most cases the defensive king should go to the short side, so that the rook can go to the long one"
... } 5. Kd6 Ra6+ 6. Kc5 Re6 *


