1. Ka6 { .
We see a position where we cannot apply Philidor. But against a knight's pawn we have a new resource: the 1st rank defense!
... } 1... Rc8! { By keeping the 1st rank covered with the rook, and the king in the squares a8-b8, there's no way for White to promote the knight pawn. } 2. b6 Rf8 3. Rb7+ Ka8! (3... Kc8?? 4. Ka7!) 4. Ra7+ Kb8 5. Rh7 Rg8 { .
And there's no way to make progress.
Note that this defensive method only works against the knight pawn. } *


