In this position, since Philidor and 1st rank are impossible, the only way to draw would be K&H (Rc1, see chapter 7), but we'll see how Rd8 fails here:

... } { [%cal Rd1d8] }
1... Rd8? (1... Rc1 { K&H }) (1... Rb1+ 2. Kc6 Kb8 { also K&H }) 2. c6 Rg8 { .
How do we win now?
Well, we use the extra file we have:
... } 3. Ra7! { [%cal Ga7a8] } 3... Kb8 4. c7+ Kc8 5. Ra8+ Kd7 6. Rxg8 *


[Event "Rook + Pawn vs Rook: Kling and Horwitz"]
[Date "2020.12.10"]
