[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/Fz9GhZVU/DraSvcNS"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/pepellou"]
[FEN "r7/3RK1k1/4P3/8/8/8/8/8 w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2020.12.10"]
[UTCTime "21:52:37"]

1. Rc7 { .
This move and Rb7 are equivalent.
This attempt gives Black many options. Every rook move on the a-file (except a7) draws, as well as Kg6.
Since a8 is such a great spot for the rook, the simplest defence is Kg6.
... } 1... Kg6! { And our next move is going to be Kg7.
White is not making progress. } *


[Event "Rook + Pawn vs Rook: Attacking #1"]
[Date "2020.12.10"]
[Result "*"]
[Variant "Standard"]
[ECO "?"]
[Opening "?"]
[StudyName "Rook + Pawn vs Rook"]
[ChapterName "Attacking #1"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/Fz9GhZVU/clNPH0ph"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/pepellou"]
[FEN "1r6/R3K1k1/4P3/8/8/8/8/8 w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2020.12.10"]
[UTCTime "21:52:37"]

{ We've said many times how this position is lost for Black because the rook is not on the a-file.

Let's see how to win.

... }
1. Kd6+! { .
It's the only move to win, but more important than the move itself is the maneuver we're trying to do: we want to get to the same position being Black's turn so the king is forced to be on g6, and only then we'll be able to initiate a winning rook maneuver.
... } 1... Kf6 (1... Kf8 2. Kd7 Kg7 3. Ke7 { it's the same }) 2. Kd7! (2. Rf7+ Kg6 3. Rf1 Ra8) 2... Kg7 (2... Rb1 3. e7 Rd1+ 4. Ke8 { [%cal Ge8f8] } 4... Kg7) 3. Ke7! { Zugzwang. } 3... Kg6 { .
Now that the king is on g6 instead of g7, we start the next phase: bring the rook behind the pawn and threaten to promote.
... } 4. Ra1! Rb7+ 5. Kd6 (5. Kd8 { would be an engine's choice since it takes less moves, but Kd6 is more forcing }) 5... Rb6+ 6. Kd7 Rb7+ 7. Kc6 Rb8 8. Kc7 Rb2 9. Re1! { .
Securing the promotion. Note that this wouldn't work with the king on g7.
... } 9... Rc2+ 10. Kd7 Rd2+ 11. Ke8 Ra2 12. e7 { Lucena } *


[Event "Rook + Pawn vs Rook: Attacking #2"]
[Date "2020.12.10"]
[Result "*"]
[Variant "Standard"]
[ECO "?"]
[Opening "?"]
