1. Kd6+ Kf6 2. Kd7 Kg6 { .
This is an interesting attempt to triangulate us back. If we go to e7 now, Black will repeat the starting position with Kg7.
But the king is already misplaced on g6, so we can start our winning rook maneuver:
... } 3. Ra1! Rb7+ 4. Kc6 Rb8 5. Kc7 { etc } 5... Rb2 6. Re1 Rc2+ 7. Kd7 Rd2+ 8. Ke8 Kf6 9. e7 { [%cal Ge8f8] } 9... Kg7 *


