[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/ppfi9AbT/ZTbHjaiW"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/pepellou"]
[FEN "5k2/q5p1/3pBp2/r2Pp1pQ/4P3/7P/5PPK/8 w - - 1 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2020.06.03"]
[UTCTime "18:27:18"]

{ Can you believe we can checkmate the king on b6 using black's queen and rook as blockers of the escape squares?

Not so difficult actually:

... } { [%csl Ra7,Ra5] }
1. Qh8+ { [%csl Re7,Ra5,Ra7,Gh8][%cal Gh5h8,Rf8e7] } 1... Ke7 { [%csl Ra5,Ra7,Gh8][%cal Gh5h8] } 2. Qxg7+ { [%csl Re8,Rd8,Ra7,Ra5,Gg7,Gh8][%cal Gh5h8,Gh8g7,Re7e8,Re7d8] } 2... Ke8 { [%csl Ra7,Ra5,Gh8,Gg7][%cal Gh5h8,Gh8g7] } 3. Qg8+ { [%csl Re7,Ra7,Ra5,Gh8,Gg7,Gg8][%cal Gh5h8,Gh8g7,Gg7g8,Re8e7] } 3... Ke7 { [%csl Ra5,Ra7,Gh8,Gg7,Gg8][%cal Gh5h8,Gh8g7,Gg7g8] } 4. Qf7+ { [%csl Rd8,Ra7,Ra5,Gh8,Gg7,Gg8,Gf7][%cal Gh5h8,Gh8g7,Gg7g8,Gg8f7,Re7d8] } 4... Kd8 { [%csl Ra5,Ra7,Gh8,Gg7,Gg8,Gf7][%cal Gh5h8,Gh8g7,Gg7g8,Gg8f7] } 5. Qf8+ { [%csl Rc7,Ra7,Ra5,Gh8,Gg7,Gg8,Gf7,Gf8][%cal Gh5h8,Gh8g7,Gg7g8,Gg8f7,Gf7f8,Rd8c7] } 5... Kc7 { [%csl Ra5,Ra7,Gh8,Gg7,Gg8,Gf7,Gf8][%cal Gh5h8,Gh8g7,Gg7g8,Gg8f7,Gf7f8] } 6. Qc8+ { [%csl Rb6,Ra7,Ra5,Gh8,Gg7,Gg8,Gf7,Gf8,Gc8][%cal Gh5h8,Gh8g7,Gg7g8,Gg8f7,Gf7f8,Gf8c8,Rc7b6,Be6c8] } 6... Kb6 { [%csl Ra5,Ra7,Gh8,Gg7,Gg8,Gf7,Gf8,Gc8][%cal Gh5h8,Gh8g7,Gg7g8,Gg8f7,Gf7f8,Gf8c8] } 7. Qc6# { [%csl Ra7,Ra5,Gc6,Gh8,Gg7,Gg8,Gf7,Gf8,Gc8][%cal Gh5h8,Gh8g7,Gg7g8,Gg8f7,Gf7f8,Gf8c8,Gc8c6,Bd5c6] } *


[Event "Checkmates - Patterns with defended queen: Do the right checks"]
[Date "2020.06.03"]
[Result "*"]
[Variant "Standard"]
[ECO "?"]
[Opening "?"]
[StudyName "Checkmates - Patterns with defended queen"]
[ChapterName "Do the right checks"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/ppfi9AbT/7glQdw3G"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/pepellou"]
[FEN "2R5/2p3k1/1p1p1pq1/2p5/6r1/2P4Q/PP4rP/R6K w - - 1 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2020.06.03"]
[UTCTime "18:27:18"]

{ There is a checkmate in 4 here, but it's important to do the right checks. The first one is obvious:

... }
1. Qh8+ { .
Diagonal check, 2 escape squares, one is blocked.
... } { [%csl Rg6,Rf7,Gh8][%cal Rg7f7,Bc8h8,Gh3h8] } 1... Kf7 { .
This is the critical decision, we can check with the queen on f8 or e8.
One should realize that checking on f8 allows the king to escape to e6 and from there to many other squares, therefore ...
... } { [%csl Gh8][%cal Gh3h8] } 2. Qe8+! { .
Keeping the king trapped close to his own pieces.
... } { [%csl Gh8,Ge8,Rf6,Rg7][%cal Gh3h8,Gh8e8,Rf7g7,Bc8e8] } 2... Kg7 { [%csl Gh8,Ge8][%cal Gh3h8,Gh8e8] } 3. Qf8+ { [%csl Gh8,Ge8,Gf8,Rg6,Rh7][%cal Gh3h8,Gh8e8,Ge8f8,Bc8f8,Rg7h7] } 3... Kh7 { .
And after 3 diagonal checks it's time for a frontal check with checkmate, in the same square where we did the first check:
... } { [%csl Gh8,Ge8,Gf8][%cal Gh3h8,Gh8e8,Ge8f8] } 4. Qh8# { [%csl Rg6,Gh8,Ge8,Gf8][%cal Bc8h8,Gh3h8,Gh8e8,Ge8f8,Gf8h8] } *


