[ChapterName "Isolated pawns"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/e7vtCGV5/vW451uIW"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/pepellou"]
[FEN "8/8/8/5k2/5P1P/8/8/K7 w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2019.05.18"]
[UTCTime "15:54:19"]

{ The chances to win with isolated pawns are also high.

Critical situations are when the opponent's king is already threatening one of the pawns. There are 2 resources to win in these situations:

1) Mutual defense of the pawns
2) Delaying capture of a pawn to allow the king to support the other pawn

In this position, we have the 1st resource (see next chapter for the 2nd)

... }
1. h5! { .
Two pawns separated by one file can defend each other as long as the king does not attack the more advanced one.
... } 1... Kf6 { [%cal Rf6g7,Rg7h6] } 2. Kb2 { [%cal Rf6g7,Rg7h6] } 2... Kg7 { [%cal Rg7h6] } 3. f5! { Necessary! } 3... Kh6 4. f6! *


