{ 1) Key squares are 3 squares on each side of the pawn. First king to arrive to them will capture the enemy pawn.

2) If you have the pawn on the 5th rank and you capture the opponent's pawn, you'll win, unless they're rook's pawns.

3) If the pawn is less advanced than the 5th rank, the defending king can draw if it reaches the right square in time. }
 *


[Event "Pawn endings (more than 1 pawn on the board): Adjacent files - sacrifice resource"]
[Date "2019.05.18"]
