{ If the passed pawn is on the central file nearest to the blocked rook's pawns, it's easier for the defending side to develop counterplay against the pawns. The approach is then very different from the previous examples.

When the pawn is on the 6th it's very favorable to the defender:

... }
1. Kc1 Kd4 2. Kc2 Kc4 3. d3+ Kd4 { .
Note that the immediate counterattack Kb5 draws easily.
We will just follow this line to demonstrate that we can draw no matter how advanced the passed pawn is.
... } 4. Kd2 Kd5 5. Kc3 Kc6?? { well, we would never do this, would we? this would be a way to lose: } (5... Kc5 6. d4+ Kd5 7. Kd3 Kd6 8. Kc4 Kc6 9. d5+ Kd6 10. Kd4 Kd7 11. Kc5 Kc7 12. d6+ Kd7 13. Kd5 Kd8 14. Kc6 Kc8 { .
Even here it's a draw:
... } 15. d7+ Kd8 16. Kb7 Kxd7 17. Kxa7 Kc7 $10) 6. Kc4 Kb6 7. Kd5 Kxa6 8. Kc6 *


