{ Winning chances increase with the pawn on the 5th rank.

If the passed pawn was on the 2nd rank, the immediate counterattack would be enough to draw. But here White can win!

... }
1. Ke2! Kc5 2. Ke3 Kd5 { passive defense also fails: } (2... Kb5 3. Kd4! Kxa5 4. Kc5! { .
Instructive sequence to remember!
Now white wins:
... } 4... Ka4 5. d4 a5 6. d5 Kb3 7. d6 a4 8. d7 a3 9. d8=Q a2 10. Qd4) 3. d4 Kd6 4. Ke4 Ke6 5. d5+ Kd6 6. Kd4 Kd7 7. Kc5 Kc7 8. d6+ Kd7 9. Kd5 Kd8 10. Kc6 Kc8 11. Kb6 Kd7 12. Kxa6 Kxd6 13. Kb7 *


