{ We had this position in chapter 29 with Black to move after White had to play g3 to regain opposition. But now it's White to move again, do we have time for another pawn tempi?

No, this is already a draw.
Let's see Black's correct defense:

... }
1. h4 (1. h3 { (no other move would make progress provided that Black has the opposition) } 1... Kg6 { (other moves would draw, but this is the simplest) } 2. Kg4 Kf6 3. Kh5 Kg7 4. Kg5 { .
A critical moment for Black. We can allow Kh6, but we must remember BIRD's RULE:
Pawns are in different colors, therefore after Kh6 we must be able to play Kg8 to put kings in different colors too:
... } 4... h6+ (4... Kh8!! 5. Kh6 Kg8 6. g4 Kh8 7. g5 Kg8 8. h4 Kh8 9. h5 Kg8 10. g6 hxg6 11. hxg6 Kh8 12. g7+ Kg8 $10) 5. Kf5 Kf7 6. g4 Kg7 7. h4 Kf7 8. h5 { [%csl Be6,Bf6,Bg6] }) 1... h5 *


