[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/pepellou"]
[FEN "8/7p/8/5k2/8/5K2/6PP/8 b - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2019.05.28"]
[UTCTime "12:06:46"]

{ Another position to remember is this one. All the pawns are still on the 2nd rank, but because Black's king is on the 4th rank, there's a drawing resource:

... }
1... h5! { (only move)
By advancing the pawn, Black's king can defend the key squares of its pawn and save the game:
... } { [%csl Bg5,Be5,Bf5] } 2. Ke3 { [%csl Be5,Bf5,Bg5] } 2... Ke5 { .
White's problem is that to win the opposition a pawn must be pushed, and then the key squares are no longer important:
... } { [%csl Bg5,Bf5,Be5] } 3. g3 { [%csl Be5,Bf5,Bg5] } (3. h3 Kf5 4. Kf3 h4 5. Ke3 Ke5) 3... Kf5 { [%csl Bg5,Bf5,Be5] } 4. Kf3 { [%csl Be5,Bg5,Bf5] } 4... Kg5 { [%csl Bf5,Bg5,Be5] } 5. Ke4 { [%csl Ge5,Bf5,Bg5] } (5. h3 Kf5 6. h4 Ke5 7. Ke3 Kf5 8. Kd4 Kg4 9. Ke5 Kxg3 $10) 5... h4! { .
And White entered a key square, but pawns get traded and it's a draw. } *


