{ Averbakh, 1972

We'll see some of the themes we already discussed and a few well-known tricks:

... }
1. Bh5!? { the only attempt to win, since the king on d8 would be an immediate draw
... } 1... Bh3 2. Ke5!? { this is the most dangerous for Black, who can hold by knowing the defensive technique of transferring the king to the rear of the pawn
... } { [%cal Ge5d4,Gd4c5,Gc5b6,Gb6c7] } 2... Bd7?! { Not immediate disaster, but waiting is not the way to draw: } (2... Kg7! { from here we know how to draw } { [%cal Rg7f6,Rf6e5] } 3. Kd5 Kf6 4. Kc5 Ke5 5. Kc6 { [%cal Ge5d4] } 5... Bf5 6. Kc7 Kd5 { [%cal Gd5c5] }) 3. Kd5 Kg7! { Still possible to draw } (3... Ba4?? 4. Kc5! { [%cal Gc5b6,Gb6c7] } 4... Bd7 5. Kb6 Ba4 6. Kc7 $18) 4. Kc5 Kf6 5. Kb6 Ke5 6. Kc7 Bh3 (6... Ba4?? 7. Bf3! Kd4 8. Bc6) 7. Be8 Kd4! 8. Bd7 Bf1 9. Bg4 Bb5 10. Bf3 Kc5 $10 *


