1. e4 Nc6 { Nimzowitsch Defense } 2. d4 d5 { Scandinavian Variation } 3. Nc3 { Bogoljubow Variation. The main move on the board. e5 is the main move online. } 3... dxe4 (3... a6? { Brandics Gambit } 4. exd5 Nb4 { [%cal Gd8d5] } 5. a3 (5. Bc4) 5... Nxd5 6. Nxd5 Qxd5 7. Nf3) (3... g6? { Erben Gambit }) (3... e5?! { Heinola-Deppe Gambit }) (3... Nf6?! { Vehre Variation }) 4. d5 (4. Nxe4?! { Bad idea! } 4... Qxd4 5. Bd3 (5. Qxd4 Nxd4) 5... Bf5 6. Nf3 Qd7 7. Qe2 { Step out of the queen exchange that would happen after Bxe4 Bxe4 Qxd1. } 7... Nf6 8. O-O Bxe4 9. Bxe4 Nxe4 10. Qxe4 e6 $15) 4... Ne5 { Nimzowitsch Gambit } (4... Nb8!? { The engine says this is better. Rarely played for obvious reasons. } 5. f3 { Richter Gambit } (5. Bf4 Nf6)) *


