1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 c5 4. c3 Nc6 5. Nf3 Qb6 { The idea is to increase the pressure on d4 and eventually undermine the white centre. The queen also attacks the b2-square, so White's dark-square bishop cannot easily defend the d4-pawn without losing the b2-pawn. } 6. a3 { currently the most important line in the Advance: it prepares 7.b4, gaining space on the queenside } (6. Be2 Nh6 { [%cal Rc5d4,Rh6f5] }) (6. Bd3 cxd4 7. cxd4 Bd7 (7... Nxd4 8. Nxd4 Qxd4 9. Bb5+ { [%cal Rd1d4] }) 8. O-O Nxd4 9. Nxd4 Qxd4 10. Nc3 { Milner-Barry Gambit } 10... Qxe5 11. Re1 { [%csl Rd5] } 11... Qb8 (11... Qd6 12. Nb5) 12. Nxd5) 6... c4 { prevents b4 (we would take en passant) } (6... Nh6) *


