1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. f4 { At grandmaster level, the move 3.f4, the Vienna Gambit, is considered too risky an opening. } (3. g3) (3. a3) (3. Nf3 { Transposes to the Petrov's Three Knights Game }) (3. Bc4 { The move 3.Bc4 leads to a position which can also be reached from the Bishop's Opening (1.e4 e5 2.Bc4) } 3... Bc5 { transposes to the King's Gambit Declined after: } (3... Nc6 4. d3 Na5 (4... Bc5) (4... d6)) 4. d3 d6 5. f4 Nc6 6. Nf3) 3... d5 (3... exf4 4. e5 Qe7 5. Qe2) 4. fxe5 Nxe4 5. Nf3 { White obtains open lines and attacking chances, but Black can usually hold the balance with correct play. } (5. Qf3 Nc6 6. Nxe4 Nd4) (5. d3) *


