{ As mentioned in the intro, opening theory is especially important in this game, given the short games and the easy to go wrong in just one move.

In many cases, a copy-cat strategy by black is the way to go for the draw. We'll see some exceptions though.

There's an amazing resource in this study with at least 52 different theoretical lines:
--[[ https://lichess.org/study/7qOrZwG6 ]]--

I will try to approach the openings study from beginner to expert though, in an incremental way. }
 *


[Event "RacingKings: from zero to hero: Main opening choices"]
[Date "2019.01.04"]
[Result "*"]
[Variant "Racing Kings"]
[ECO "?"]
[Opening "?"]
[StudyName "RacingKings: from zero to hero"]
[ChapterName "Main opening choices"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/smcFoj9R/w9MbMfrK"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/pepellou"]
