[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2019.01.04"]
[UTCTime "02:20:31"]

{ Some topics I'd like to explore, as they strike me as fundamentally different from regular chess:

- There are no endgames
- What pieces can be captured matter a lot when it comes to tactics
- A piece out of the board can be more "active" than a piece in the board (it has access to more squares)
- Material is not important; king safety is }
 *


